Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.name: log(_:at:file:function:line:column:)
Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.abstract: Logs an encodable at the provided log level The encodable can be encoded to the required format.

Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.name: verbose(_:file:function:line:column:)
Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.abstract: Verbose logs are used to log tiny, usually irrelevant information.

Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.name: debug(_:file:function:line:column:)
Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.abstract: Debug logs are used to debug problems

Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.name: info(_:file:function:line:column:)
Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.abstract: Info logs are used to indicate a specific infrequent event occurring.

Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.name: warning(_:file:function:line:column:)
Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.abstract: Warnings are used to indicate something should be fixed but may not have to be solved yet

Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.name: error(_:file:function:line:column:)
Protocols/Logger.html#/s:7Logging6Logger.abstract: Error, indicates something went wrong and a part of the execution was failed.
